RACE.RACE_TEXT: MIDDLEBURG RACE 1 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 142 lbs.; Four Year Olds, 150 lbs.; Older, 154 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRESS PAUSE (FR) led from the start always clear of the field, drew off impressively after the final hurdle for an easy victory. LOOK NORTH tracked the leader, gave chase but was no match for the winner. IMPERIAL ASSASSIN (IRE) went unhurried early, rated and gave a strong finishing rally. MR JEFFERSON was rated and produced a mild late gain passing tired ones. ABSAM was rated, rallied going to the last fence, then stopped. PRAGHAS CEART (IRE) was no threat and dropped back. THALEEQ (GB) traveled up with the pace on the first circuit then tired two hurdles out. OUTPERFORM trailed. TRANSIT traveled mid-pack the tired and dropped back.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: KIYOMORI stalked the pacesetter on the first circuit, waited, launched a bid going into the last hurdle and closed with a rush in stretch to get up at the wire. FOXY WALK (IRE) battled into the final fence, held the lead briefly and persisted through stretch to hold second place. I CAN ONLY IMAGINE (IRE) rated mid pack, bid and drew even, then outfinished in the stretch run. QUICK MASTER had a wide trip and finished evenly. TRAVESURAS was no threat. GO TAKE CHARGE raced greenly and trailed. SLEIGHT OF HAND trailed and finished tired. FINDING FREEDOM led the first circuit, then tired two hurdles out. SEATTLE SEAHAWK (IRE) was hard to settle, tired, dropped back, pulled up and was vanned off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: MIDDLEBURG RACE 3 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Handicap Purse 30000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH ARE RATED 115 OR LOWER. The highest rated horse will be assigned 158 lbs. with all other weights adjusted accordingly based on the current ratings. Minimum weight 140 lbs., not including a pprentice allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EYE OF GUNFIGHTER tracked leader in second on the first circuit, assumed command on the final circuit, repelled all challengers. SOUTH MOUNTAIN (IRE) rated, rallied two hurdles out, gave chase, held second. PING PONG CHAMP under persistent pressure three wide in the stretch to get up for third. SEISMIC WAVE reserved and produced a mild finishing rally. WITHOUTDESTINATION (GB) traveld mid pack, ridden to contention at the final fence, then weakened. FRONTLINE CITIZEN (IRE) traveled evenly and did not threaten. LEFT BLANK rated, was ridden forward into the final hurdle, then tired and dropped back. SEIZING THE DREAM trailed. VINCENT VAN GOGO showed speed in the lead for the first circuit, tired and was pulled up before the last jump. ARROWHEART fell mid race.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNION GEN. GEORGE moved up on the final circuit, drew even at the final fence, dueled in an all out drive through the stretch for the win. SCOTTY trailed throughout and was pulled up. LAKER MAMBA raced greenly, fell on the final circuit.
